    "slug": "intense-downpour-weather",
    "description": "<p><strong>Intense Downpour</strong> is a storm of Biblical proportions. An absurdly heavy downpour that smothers flames and causes Trainers to regret not bringing their water wings. Extremely beneficial to Water-Types and strong swimmers.</p><p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Effects:</span></strong></p><ul><li>For the purposes of Abilities, Attacks, Perks, and Traits, this Weather is considered to also be “Rainy”.</li><li>Water-Type Attacks deal 60% more damage, and Fire-Type Attacks fail to activate when declared.</li><li>Non-[Contact] Electric-Type Attacks have +60% Range (minimum +2).</li><li>All [Explode] Attacks fail to activate when declared.</li><li>All Water-Type have their Swim Allowance increased by 60% (minimum 2)</li><li>All creatures may utilize Swim Movement in place of their Overland Movement. All creatures without [Hover] are Grounded, and all creatures have their non-Swim Allowances reduced by 50% (Movement Scores can only reach a minimum of 3).</li><li>Physical-Category Attacks suffer an additional -1 ACC from RIP, and have their Range decreased by 30% (minimum Range is the creature’s Reach).</li></ul>"
  },
